install xf86-input-wacom (driver)
install linux-headers (to install kernel modules)
install input-wacom-dkms from aur (has kernel modules)

ta fucking da

(I used to have xorg conf files and things, included in this folder,
but they apparently aren't necessary (and didn't do anything anyway,
according to xorg logs.))

For more:
https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Wacom_tablet
